# Tuned for the Nest-Mini-style voice-assistant workload.
# Parent handles the bulk of the weights; we cap parameters + system prompt here.
FROM qwen3:1.7b

# The default is 40,960 tokens (≈9 GB KV cache at fp16 on Qwen3-1.7B's
# 28 layers × 2048 hidden_dim). On a Pi 4/8 GB, that would OOM-Kill
# the JVM orchestrator or the LVA process. 2,048 yields ~450 MB of KV
# and is plentiful for system-prompt + short turns of history.
PARAMETER num_ctx 2048

# Cap reply length so TTS never spools forever; voice replies should
# be 1-3 sentences, ~256 tokens is a generous ceiling.
PARAMETER num_predict 256

# Qwen3 supports a "thinking" mode that emits chain-of-thought before
# the final answer. We disable it for the assistant path: Piper would
# otherwise attempt to start speaking the internal reasoning.
PARAMETER temperature 0.6
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

SYSTEM """You are a privacy-first voice assistant running on a Raspberry Pi.
Reply in 1-3 short, conversational sentences. No markdown, no lists, no code blocks.
If you don't know the answer, say so plainly; do not invent."""
